# Import path aliases

Configured in `tsconfig.json` (`paths`):

- `@common/*` → `src/common/*`
- `@modules/*` → `src/modules/*`

When importing from those folders, use these aliases instead of deep relative paths (`../../common/...`, `../modules/...`).

```typescript
// Prefer
import { CryptoService } from '@common/crypto/crypto.service';
import { UsersService } from '@modules/users/users.service';

// Avoid
import { CryptoService } from '../../common/crypto/crypto.service';
```

Do not introduce new relative traversals across `src/common` or `src/modules` when an alias applies.
